	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Requirement_assignment_arm  Entity: Requirement_assignment  
   <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment">
A <b>Requirement_assignment</b> is used to relate a requirement (via the <express_ref linkend="requirement_view_definition:arm:Requirement_view_definition_arm.Requirement_view_definition"/> entity) to data types representing the items
which are affected by the requirement.
<example>
A requirement "the vehicle shall have a maximum power output of at least 150BHP" could be assigned to the data types
which are used to represent the vehicle's engine.
</example>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Requirement_assignment_arm  Entity: Requirement_assignment  Attribute: assigned_requirement 
   <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment.assigned_requirement"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment.assigned_requirement">
the <express_ref linkend="requirement_view_definition:arm:Requirement_view_definition_arm.Requirement_view_definition"/> which is assigned.
</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Requirement_assignment_arm  Entity: Requirement_assignment  Attribute: assigned_to 
   <express_ref linkend="requirement_assignment:arm:Requirement_assignment_arm.Requirement_assignment.assigned_to"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
